# Spring Annotations 🏷️

## 📖 What are Spring Annotations?

**Spring Annotations** are special metadata that provide instructions to the Spring Framework.

They reduce XML configuration and make Spring applications easier to develop and maintain.

In simple words:

> **Annotations tell Spring what to do automatically.**

---

# 🎯 Why Use Annotations?

Without Annotations:

❌ XML Configuration

❌ Manual Bean Registration

❌ More Boilerplate Code

❌ Complex Configuration

With Annotations:

✅ Less Configuration

✅ Automatic Bean Management

✅ Dependency Injection

✅ Faster Development

---

# 🏗 Spring Annotation Architecture

```text id="sa1"
Spring Application
        │
        ▼
Annotations
        │
        ├── @Component
        ├── @Service
        ├── @Repository
        ├── @Controller
        ├── @RestController
        ├── @Autowired
        ├── @Bean
        ├── @Configuration
        ├── @Primary
        └── @Qualifier
```

---

# 🏷 @Component

Marks a class as a Spring Bean.

```java id="sa2"
import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;

@Component
public class Student {

}
```

Spring automatically creates and manages this Bean.

---

# 🏷 @Service

Used for the Service Layer (Business Logic).

```java id="sa3"
import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;

@Service
public class StudentService {

}
```

---

# 🏷 @Repository

Used for the Data Access Layer.

```java id="sa4"
import org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;

@Repository
public class StudentRepository {

}
```

It also provides automatic exception translation.

---

# 🏷 @Controller

Used in Spring MVC applications.

Returns Views (HTML Pages).

```java id="sa5"
import org.springframework.stereotype.Controller;

@Controller
public class HomeController {

}
```

---

# 🏷 @RestController

Used for REST APIs.

It combines:

```text id="sa6"
@RestController
        │
        ├── @Controller
        └── @ResponseBody
```

Example:

```java id="sa7"
@RestController
public class StudentController {

    @GetMapping("/")
    public String home() {
        return "Welcome";
    }

}
```

Output:

```text id="sa8"
Welcome
```

---

# 🏷 @Autowired

Automatically injects dependencies.

```java id="sa9"
@Service
class StudentService {

}

@RestController
class StudentController {

    @Autowired
    private StudentService service;

}
```

---

# 🏷 @Bean

Manually creates a Spring Bean.

```java id="sa10"
@Configuration
public class AppConfig {

    @Bean
    public Student student() {
        return new Student();
    }

}
```

---

# 🏷 @Configuration

Marks a class as a Spring Configuration class.

```java id="sa11"
@Configuration
public class AppConfig {

}
```

Usually contains `@Bean` methods.

---

# 🏷 @Primary

Specifies the default Bean when multiple Beans exist.

```java id="sa12"
@Component
@Primary
class DieselEngine {

}
```

---

# 🏷 @Qualifier

Selects a specific Bean.

```java id="sa13"
@Autowired
@Qualifier("dieselEngine")
private Engine engine;
```

---

# 🏷 @ComponentScan

Tells Spring where to scan for Components.

```java id="sa14"
@ComponentScan("com.anup")
```

---

# 🏷 @SpringBootApplication

Main annotation in Spring Boot.

It combines:

```text id="sa15"
@SpringBootApplication
        │
        ├── @Configuration
        ├── @EnableAutoConfiguration
        └── @ComponentScan
```

Example:

```java id="sa16"
@SpringBootApplication
public class DemoApplication {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        SpringApplication.run(
            DemoApplication.class,
            args
        );

    }

}
```

---

# 🏷 @RequestMapping

Maps HTTP requests.

```java id="sa17"
@RequestMapping("/students")
```

---

# 🏷 @GetMapping

Handles HTTP GET requests.

```java id="sa18"
@GetMapping("/students")
public String getStudents() {
    return "Students";
}
```

---

# 🏷 @PostMapping

Handles HTTP POST requests.

```java id="sa19"
@PostMapping("/students")
```

---

# 🏷 @PutMapping

Handles HTTP PUT requests.

```java id="sa20"
@PutMapping("/students")
```

---

# 🏷 @DeleteMapping

Handles HTTP DELETE requests.

```java id="sa21"
@DeleteMapping("/students")
```

---

# 🏷 @PathVariable

Extracts values from URL.

```java id="sa22"
@GetMapping("/students/{id}")
public String getStudent(
        @PathVariable int id) {

    return "ID : " + id;
}
```

---

# 🏷 @RequestParam

Reads query parameters.

```java id="sa23"
@GetMapping("/students")
public String student(
    @RequestParam String name) {

    return name;
}
```

URL:

```text id="sa24"
http://localhost:8080/students?name=Anup
```

---

# 🏷 @RequestBody

Converts JSON into Java Object.

```java id="sa25"
@PostMapping("/students")
public Student saveStudent(
        @RequestBody Student student){

    return student;

}
```

---

# 🏷 @ResponseBody

Returns data directly instead of a view.

```java id="sa26"
@ResponseBody
public String home() {
    return "Hello";
}
```

---

# 🏷 @Value

Injects values from properties file.

```java id="sa27"
@Value("${server.port}")
private String port;
```

---

# 🏷 @Profile

Loads Beans based on active profiles.

```java id="sa28"
@Profile("dev")
@Component
public class DevConfig {

}
```

---

# 🏷 @Lazy

Creates Bean only when required.

```java id="sa29"
@Lazy
@Component
public class Student {

}
```

---

# 🏷 @Scope

Defines Bean Scope.

```java id="sa30"
@Scope("prototype")
@Component
public class Student {

}
```

